<task id="UDSS-001" project="UI Dialog Shell Standardization">
  <metadata>
    <title>Define IDataService, IUploadService, INavigationService interfaces</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>shared-library, types, architecture</tags>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Define the core service abstraction interfaces (IDataService, IUploadService, INavigationService)
    in the @spaarke/ui-components shared library types directory. These interfaces decouple wizard
    components from direct Xrm.WebApi calls, enabling portability across Code Pages, PCF controls,
    and test environments. IDataService covers CRUD operations, IUploadService handles file upload
    and container resolution, and INavigationService wraps dialog and record navigation.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior TypeScript developer with Dataverse platform experience</role>

  <goal>
    Three interface files exist in src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/types/, are exported
    from the types barrel, and the project compiles cleanly with tsc --noEmit.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">All shared components must use service portability tiers — no direct Xrm.WebApi calls in shared library code.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Interfaces must be generic enough to support Xrm, REST, and mock adapters without leaking platform types.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/types/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read existing types in src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/types/ to understand current type conventions and barrel structure.</step>
    <step id="2">Create IDataService interface with methods: createRecord(entityName, data), retrieveRecord(entityName, id, select?, expand?), retrieveMultipleRecords(entityName, options?, maxPageSize?), updateRecord(entityName, id, data), deleteRecord(entityName, id). All methods return Promise.</step>
    <step id="3">Create IUploadService interface with methods: uploadFile(entityName, recordId, fileAttributeName, file, containerType?), getContainerIdForEntity(entityName, recordId).</step>
    <step id="4">Create INavigationService interface with methods: openRecord(entityName, recordId), openDialog(webResourceName, params, dialogOptions), closeDialog(returnValue?).</step>
    <step id="5">Export all three interfaces from types/index.ts barrel file.</step>
    <step id="6">Run tsc --noEmit to verify compilation succeeds with no type errors.</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>IDataService interface exists with createRecord, retrieveRecord, retrieveMultipleRecords, updateRecord, deleteRecord methods.</criterion>
    <criterion>IUploadService interface exists with uploadFile and getContainerIdForEntity methods.</criterion>
    <criterion>INavigationService interface exists with openRecord, openDialog, closeDialog methods.</criterion>
    <criterion>All interfaces are exported from types/index.ts barrel.</criterion>
    <criterion>tsc --noEmit passes with zero errors.</criterion>
    <criterion>No direct Xrm type references in the interface definitions.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
